(659, 0, 586, 29780, 1, '[#29780] Contact Search Filter - Category View Failed?', '<p>I think I have stumbled on an issue with the search filter displayed in the Contacts listing for a specific category.  I''m relatively new to this so please forgive any mistakes.</p>\n\n<p>J!3.0.2</p>\n\n<p>When a menu item created for listing contacts of a specific category, the Search input box was displayed.  I wasn''t able to find the switch to hide this and any input was ignored as far as filtering was concerned.</p>\n\n<p>default_items.php view had the following line of code</p>\n\n<p>&lt;?php if ($this-&gt;params-&gt;get(''filter_field'') != ''hide'') :?&gt;</p>\n\n<p>There was no parameter "filter_field" in the xml files (default.xml or config.xml).</p>\n\n<p>Insert following into admin/config.xml at around line 433</p>\n\n<pre><code>        &lt;field name="filter_field" type="radio"\n            default="1"\n            class="btn-group"\n            label="COM_CONTACT_FIELD_FILTER_FIELD_LABEL"\n
