(1386, 10917426, 154, 'SvenRtbg', 'comment', '<p>The point everyone misses is this: Using a session in more than one concurrent request requires proper locking. Otherwise, a situation like this destroys data: Two requests both read the session data first, then both change different things in the session, and after a different runtime, both try to save to the storage. The request saving last wins.</p>\n\n<p>This problem is included in ALL Joomla session storage modules with the exception of the "None" module, because neither acquires an exclusive lock on the session data when executing "open()" and releases it when executing "close()".</p>', '2012-12-01 14:03:00'),
