(1569, 5894373, 214, 'Twentronix', 'comment', '<p>Test instructions (J!2.5)</p>\n\n<p>1- Overwrite your J2.5 files:<br><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/214/files">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/214/files</a><br>\n2- Go to article manager in back-end Joomla. <br>\n3- Options -&gt; Integration -&gt; JGLOBAL_FEED_SHOW_READMORE_LABEL: Show<br>\n4- Add some articles, split them with readmore. Create menu-item of type<br>\ncategory. Maybe you need to use the syndication module to get the RSS feed<br>\nlink.<br>\n5- Go to your RSS feed for that category with Firefox:<br>\nview-source:<a href="http://your-rss-feed.com">http://your-rss-feed.com</a><br>\n6- Now you can see the read more links in the descriptions. You can turn them<br>\noff with step 3.</p>', '2012-05-24 07:27:41'),
