(2232, 10902095, 582, 'mbabker', 'comment', '<p>Some constants, like those, are application specific.  So, they do point to different paths based on the application (hence the reason each app has its own defines.php).  What would you suggest to get around this without breaking B/C at this point in time?</p>', '2012-11-30 20:07:39'),
(2233, 10914013, 582, 'dongilbert', 'comment', '<p>That''s a great question - I don''t think there IS anything to do to fix it now without breaking B\\C. Possibly add in new defines in the administrative section, and urge people to use that instead. Maybe <code>JPATH_ADMIN_TEMPLATE</code>, <code>JPATH_ADMIN_BASE</code>, etc... I''m not sure of the further implications this would cause - it''s probably best to stick with things as is with the current CMS structure. But it should be something to consider for "Joomla Next" (as Andrew likes to cal it)</p>\n\n<p>I understand you point about being application specific. However, I''ve never been a fan of the idea that the administrator is a separate "application" from the front end. It has it''s advantages and disadvantages, but I don''t like it much. I know a lot of that is carryover from Mambo and hopefully it''s something that can be addressed when rebuilding the structure of the CMS; the idea of which has been tossed around recently that the CMS in it''s current form is on it''s last legs.</p>\n\n<p>So - that said - I guess I just wanted to vent a little - thanks for listening.</p>', '2012-12-01 06:04:47'),
